  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "In the context of the Staff Selection Commission (SSC) in India, various postings or positions are available across different government departments and ministries. Here are some of the prominent postings that candidates can aspire to through SSC examinations:\n\n1. **SSC CGL (Combined Graduate Level)**:\n   - Assistant Audit Officer\n   - Assistant Accounts Officer\n   - Inspector of Income Tax\n   - Inspector (Central Excise)\n   - Inspector (Preventive Officer)\n   - Tax Assistant\n   - Sub-Inspector in CBI\n   - Assistant Section Officer (CSS)\n   - and many others.\n\n2. **SSC CHSL (Combined Higher Secondary Level)**:\n   - Data Entry Operator (DEO)\n   - Lower Division Clerk (LDC)\n   - Postal Assistant/Sorting Assistant\n\n3. **SSC JE (Junior Engineer)**:\n   - Junior Engineer in various departments like civil, mechanical, and electrical engineering.\n\n4. **SSC MTS (Multi-Tasking Staff)**:\n   - Multi-Tasking Staff in various ministries and departments.\n\n5. **SSC CPO (Central Police Organization)**:\n   - Sub-Inspector in Delhi Police\n   - Sub-Inspector in CAPFs (Central Armed Police Forces)\n\n6. **SSC Stenographer**:\n   - Stenographer Grade \u2018C\u2019 and Grade \u2018D\u2019 positions in various government offices.\n\n7. **SSC Constable GD**:\n   - Constable in various forces like CRPF, BSF, CISF, and others.\n\nThe specific postings can vary based on the annual recruitment cycle and the needs of the government. Each of these positions comes with its own eligibility criteria, responsibilities, and career progression opportunities.",
